    "summary": "I am a seasoned strategy & operations team leader with experience in establishing high-profile international culture & creative sectors initiatives. I focus on cultural transformations that nurture creativity, foster international exchanges, promote assets and contribute to economic, environmental & social development. \nI have a track record in developing culture strategies & masterplans, in conceptualising, delivering & managing complex portfolios of culture activities, including policy setting & evaluation, research & ideation, creative ecosystem stimulation & education, large scale events & exhibitions, operational innovation & digitisation, strategic partnerships, funds definition & execution, and international relations. I have a passion for building multidisciplinary teams & creating environments that inspire people to produce their best work. \n\nI led teams of 130+ nationalities to produce 800+ projects in world-class venues (incl. Louvre, Pompidou, UNESCO heritage sites) featuring 6,000+ talents (from Oscar winners to Series B entrepreneurs) resulting in 350m\u20ac+ revenues. Average 95% NPS.\n\nAchievements\n\u2022 Coordinated Paris opening cultural season for 7 years; each year: 50 world-class venues, 450 shows, 35m\u20ac, 600+ talents, 500,000+ attendees.\n\u2022 Branded the \u00ab Institut Fran\u00e7ais \u00bb to unify communication & revenue model of 143 organisations worldwide.\n\u2022 Launched 2 pan-African culture policies to nurture inter-sectorial collaborations, and activate environmental & ecological strategies.\n\u2022 Contributed to 3 innovation-led turnaround in creative industries to establish digital workplace, content collaboration; avg +25% efficiency.\n\u2022 Established 1 in-house events studio, recruited 38 FTEs to experiment & deliver 50-70 projects per year.\n\u2022 Set 10 innovation pipelines for cultural entrepreneurs: 1 venture studio, 4 corporate-university partnerships, 2 entrepreneur-in-residence programs, 3 deal sourcing global networks, brought 100+ ventures from 0 to 1.\n\nSpecialties: cultural planning | international partnerships | global events executive production | impact strategy | in-depth market research & analysis | sponsorship | triple-bottom line (people, planet, profit) | cross-functional collaboration | learning & development | brand strategy | creative direction & cultural leadership | complexity & system thinking | design-thinking | international business development, ESG, DEI, innovation.",
